text: The Jõelähtme River (also known as Raasiku jõgi or Jõelehtme jõgi) is an Estonian river in the county of Harjumaa. The river starts in Rasivere (Anija Parish) and discharges in the Jägala River in Jõelähtme Parish, only a after the Jägala Waterfall. Category:Rivers of Estonia Category:Landforms of Harju County
title: Jõelähtme River
